# Navigation Rules

This project uses **AutoRoute**. All navigation must go through it — no raw `Navigator` calls.

## Screen annotation

Every screen that can be navigated to MUST be annotated with `@RoutePage()`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/features/onboarding/presentation/screens/onboarding_screen.dart
@RoutePage()
class OnboardingScreen extends StatelessWidget { ... }

// ❌ BAD — no annotation, AutoRoute won't generate a route for it
class OnboardingScreen extends StatelessWidget { ... }

// ❌ BAD — wrong suffix
class OnboardingPage extends StatelessWidget { ... }  // use Screen, not Page
```

- Screens live in `lib/src/features/<feature>/presentation/screens/`
- File suffix: `_screen.dart` — class suffix: `Screen`
- ❌ Never use `_page.dart` / `Page` suffix

---

## Route declaration

All routes are declared in `lib/src/config/router/app_router.dart`. Never add routes anywhere else.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — app_router.dart
@AutoRouterConfig(replaceInRouteName: 'Screen,Route')
class AppRouter extends RootStackRouter {
  @override
  List<AutoRoute> get routes => [
    AutoRoute(page: MainNavigationRoute.page, initial: true, guards: [_authGuard],
      children: [
        AutoRoute(page: HomeRoute.page, path: 'home', initial: true),
        AutoRoute(page: ProfileRoute.page, path: 'profile'),
      ],
    ),
    AutoRoute(page: OnboardingRoute.page, path: '/onboarding'),
  ];
}

// ❌ BAD — route declared outside AppRouter
final router = GoRouter(routes: [...]);   // wrong library
```

Generated route name: `OnboardingScreen` → `OnboardingRoute` (suffix `Screen` → `Route`).

## Navigation API — context.router only

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
context.router.push(const OnboardingRoute());
context.router.replace(const HomeRoute());
context.router.pop();
context.router.replaceAll([const MainNavigationRoute()]); // reset stack (e.g. after login)
context.router.pushAndPopUntil(ProfileRoute(), predicate: (_) => false);

// ❌ BAD — raw Navigator
Navigator.of(context).push(MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => OnboardingScreen()));
Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/onboarding');
Navigator.pushReplacement(context, ...);
```

## Route parameters

Pass parameters via typed route constructor arguments — never via widget constructor or BLoC event.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — route with typed params (declared in app_router.dart)
AutoRoute(page: RouteDetailRoute.page, path: '/routes/:id')

// Generated usage:
context.router.push(RouteDetailRoute(routeId: route.id));

// In the screen — receive via @PathParam / @QueryParam
@RoutePage()
class RouteDetailScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  final String routeId;
  const RouteDetailScreen({@PathParam('id') required this.routeId, super.key});
}

// ❌ BAD — passing data through widget constructor outside AutoRoute
Navigator.push(context, MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => RouteDetailScreen(routeId: '123')));
```

## Navigation belongs in UI — never in BLoC or UseCase

BLoC emits state; the UI listens and navigates. BLoC must not hold a router reference.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
BlocListener<LoginBloc, LoginState>(
  listenWhen: (prev, curr) => curr.status == StateStatus.success && prev.status != curr.status,
  listener: (context, state) => context.router.replaceAll([const MainNavigationRoute()]),
  child: ...,
)

// ❌ BAD — router injected into BLoC
class LoginBloc extends Bloc<LoginEvent, LoginState> {
  final AppRouter _router;
  void _onSuccess(...) => _router.replaceAll([...]); // ❌
}
```

## Route guards

Guards live in `lib/src/config/router/` and extend `AutoRouteGuard`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/config/router/auth_guard.dart
class AuthGuard extends AutoRouteGuard {
  @override
  void onNavigation(NavigationResolver resolver, StackRouter router) async {
    final token = await _tokenStorage.getAccessToken();
    token != null && token.isNotEmpty
        ? resolver.next(true)
        : router.replaceAll([const OnboardingRoute()]);
  }
}
// ❌ BAD — auth check inside initState or BLoC```

## Tab navigation

Use `AutoTabsScaffold` for bottom-tab layouts. Tab switching via `tabsRouter.setActiveIndex()`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — MainNavigationScreen
AutoTabsScaffold(
  routes: [HomeRoute(), ProfileRoute()],
  bottomNavigationBuilder: (context, tabsRouter) => NavBar(
    initialPage: tabsRouter.activeIndex,
    onPageChanged: (index) => tabsRouter.setActiveIndex(index),
    items: [...],
  ),
)

// ❌ BAD
PageView(controller: _pageController, ...) // manual tab management
```
